definitions.definition: ( linguistics ) An extinct branch of the Indo-European language family, consisting of two languages, Tocharian A and Tocharian B , written in an abugida derived from Brahmi .

main_definition: ( linguistics ) An extinct branch of the Indo-European language family, consisting of two languages, Tocharian A and Tocharian B , written in an abugida derived from Brahmi .

definitions.definition: Any member of a people who inhabited the Tarim Basin and spoke Tocharian.

main_definition: Any member of a people who inhabited the Tarim Basin and spoke Tocharian.
